How to read this graph (quickly)
	•	Kernel Triad is the chassis (E/F/S).
	•	Mirror + Checksum + MerkleWarden + Blacksmith are the integrity spine.
	•	Spider/Hound/Dragonfly/Goblin are the primary “organs.”
	•	Ratchet + Reversibility Gate + ABL are the control laws that keep it real.
	•	Mirage + Cognitive Geometry are your diagnostic math for “AGI-feel vs true stability.”

If you want, I can also output:
	•	a minimal graph (only top 20 nodes), or
	•	a graph schema (node types, edge types, invariants), so it becomes a living spec instead of a picture.